00:00:00.587 --> 00:00:03.860
- [Voiceover] "The following
equation shows Kepler's 3rd Law

00:00:03.860 --> 00:00:05.987
"of planetary motion.

00:00:05.987 --> 00:00:10.107
"It relates the time, t (in days),

00:00:10.107 --> 00:00:13.416
"that a planet takes to
revolve once around our sun

00:00:13.416 --> 00:00:16.318
"to the distance, d (in kilometers),

00:00:16.318 --> 00:00:18.084
"of that planet from the sun."

00:00:18.084 --> 00:00:22.240
So, it tells us, t, how many
days, and it's in relation

00:00:22.240 --> 00:00:24.841
to the distance that that
planet, in kilometers,

00:00:24.841 --> 00:00:26.304
is from the sun.

00:00:26.304 --> 00:00:29.624
"Mars is approximately 4 times as distant

00:00:29.624 --> 00:00:32.038
"from the sun as Mercury is.

00:00:32.498 --> 00:00:34.221
"About how many times longer would

00:00:34.221 --> 00:00:37.751
"Mars's revolution time
be than for Mercury?

00:00:37.751 --> 00:00:41.442
"Round your answer to the
nearest whole number."

00:00:41.922 --> 00:00:43.508
So, let's think about it a little bit.

00:00:43.508 --> 00:00:47.712
If you increased d by a factor of four,

00:00:48.432 --> 00:00:51.288
if you increased d by a factor of four,

00:00:51.688 --> 00:00:53.748
what's going to happen to t?

00:00:54.478 --> 00:00:57.060
Well, if you increase
d by a factor of four,

00:00:57.060 --> 00:00:59.879
you're going to notice you
take d to the third power.

00:00:59.879 --> 00:01:02.246
So if you replace d with 4d,

00:01:02.696 --> 00:01:04.150
so if you replace it with 4d,

00:01:04.150 --> 00:01:07.216
you're going to get t squared is equal

00:01:07.216 --> 00:01:10.056
to 3.98,

00:01:10.056 --> 00:01:13.097
times 10 to the negative 20,

00:01:13.697 --> 00:01:17.276
times 4d to the third power.

00:01:17.276 --> 00:01:19.273
Well, 4d to the third power,

00:01:19.273 --> 00:01:21.038
four is going to be the same thing,

00:01:21.038 --> 00:01:24.288
I could rewrite that as four to the third,

00:01:24.288 --> 00:01:25.705
times d to the third.

00:01:25.705 --> 00:01:29.838
Four to the third power, that's
16 times four, that's 64.

00:01:30.258 --> 00:01:32.810
So, it's going to be the same thing as 64,

00:01:33.740 --> 00:01:35.317
times d to the third power.

00:01:35.317 --> 00:01:38.939
Or I could just write this
as d to the third power,

00:01:39.489 --> 00:01:42.515
and then all of that times 64.

00:01:43.425 --> 00:01:45.835
Now, we have to be careful here.

00:01:45.835 --> 00:01:48.041
We might say, "Hey, look, this expression

00:01:48.041 --> 00:01:50.967
